- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about creating bipedal robots and generating gaits for them. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses model-based trajectory optimization to generate gaits. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with under-actuated planar biped models. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions embodied movement analysis, which could involve computer vision techniques. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions conducting user studies to validate the generated gaits.
